          <title>La gemación</title>
          <description><![CDATA[<div class="text" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 10px; float: left; width: 561.25px; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">
<ul>
	<li style="border: 0px; outline: none; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px 15px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: arial; font-size: 14px; line-height: 23px;"><span style="font-size: 20px;"><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">Pueden llevarla a cabo organismos <strong>unicelulares </strong>y <strong>pluricelulares</strong></span></span></li>
</ul>

<ul>
	<li style="border: 0px; outline: none; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px 15px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: arial; font-size: 14px; line-height: 23px;"><span style="font-size: 20px;"><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">El organismo forma una&nbsp;</span></span><strong style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 20px;">gema </strong><span style="font-size:20px;">o</span><strong style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 20px;">&nbsp;yema</strong><span style="font-size: 20px;"><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">&nbsp;en alguna parte de s&iacute; mismo, que se&nbsp;desarrolla y&nbsp;convierte en un nuevo individuo&nbsp;</span></span></li>
</ul>

<ul>
	<li style="border: 0px; outline: none; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px 15px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: arial; font-size: 14px; line-height: 23px;"><span style="font-size: 20px;"><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">La yema puede permanecer&nbsp;<strong>adherida</strong>&nbsp;al organismo que le dio origen o&nbsp;<strong>i</strong><strong>ndependizarse</strong>&nbsp;de &eacute;l</span></span></li>
</ul>
</div>
]]></description>
